results.name: Product of numerator and denominator of the n-th harmonic number, 1 + 1/2 + 1/3 +...+ 1/n.
comment: Numerator and denominator in definition have no common divisors >1.
example: The 3rd harmonic number is 11/6. So a(3) = 11 * 6 = 66.
program: (PARI) a(n) = my(h=sum(k=1, n, 1/k)); numerator(h) * denominator(h); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Sep 07 2019
